===Aircraft Carriers (CV)===
*An Aircraft Carrier's Role as a Support here is of the following:
**Be able to take down Enemies with ease in Node J.
**To be able to bring {{YellowPlane}}{{EquipmentLink|Saiun}} in order to disable <span style="color:red">Red T Disadvantage</span>.
**Take out Non-Submarine Enemies in Submarine Nodes D / F / K via Opening Airstrike, and not interfere any further.
====Things to Watch Out For====
*'''DO NOT BRING A LIGHT CARRIER (CVL) or ARMORED CARRIER (CVB)!'''
**Due to the fact CVLs can attack Submarines, they will ruin your Flagship DD/CL's Attack Pattern in the Submarine Nodes, which will result in MVP loss.
**CVBs are just too expensive to use as a Support for Power Leveling, especially more so since you are already bringing a Battleship.
*Avoid using expensive Carriers like {{ShipLink|Kaga}} and {{ShipLink|Akagi}} for the sake of resource consumption per run, but if you have no choice due to lacking other properly leveled Carriers, then please use them at your discretion.
**You may lower the Resource Cost per run if you choose to bring only 1 CV.
*'''DO NOT USE POWERFUL BOMBERS!'''
**Powerful Bombers such as {{EquipmentLink|Ryuusei Kai}} and {{EquipmentLink|Tenzan Model 12 (Tomonaga Squadron)}} can result in your Aircraft Carrier stealing MVP in Submarine Nodes due to their high potential to bring out an overwhelming damage output.
***You can use them however if you choose to bring only 1 Bomber on your CV.
**You are recommended to use Average Bombers such as {{EquipmentLink|Type 97 Torpedo Bomber (Skilled)}}, and {{EquipmentLink|Tenzan}}.
***Please note that even then, by rare occurence, the CV may still somehow be able to steal MVP...
