===Support Light Cruisers===
*Due to World 4-3's Branching Rules, you are only allowed to bring 1 maximum Destroyer to be able to take the route to Nodes D / F / K. Even if you were leveling a Light Cruiser, bringing a Destroyer as Support is a bad idea.
*The Supporting Light Cruiser's job is to help take down any outstanding Submarines that the Main Flagship you are leveling cannot take down due to the limit of how many times she can attack.
**Please note that sometimes a Support Light Cruiser can steal MVP if the Main Flagship by some unfortunate RNG, has one of her attacks miss against the enemy Submarine(s). 
**When facing Enemy Submarines Pattern #1 in Nodes D / F / K, there are times where a Support Light Cruiser may not be able to fully take down the remaining Enemy Submarines which will only result in A-Rank Victory (resulting in 990 EXP instead of 1188 EXP from S-Rank), which case can be common when the Battle is under Head-On engagement, or if the Support Light Cruiser outright causes her attack(s) to miss by some unfortunate RNG.
*It is recommended that you bring a full-fledged Light Cruiser who has gone through full [[Modernization]] (Anti-Air is optional), and is fully remodeled.
