==Facts to Consider==

*Going to Node F or J from the start is completely '''RANDOM'''. There is absolutely no Branching rules that lets you avoid going to node J. 
*Bringing CAV will take you from node J to K, which means only one submarine node. '''<span style="color:red">DO NOT BRING CAV</span>'''.
*Bringing 2 or more DD will take you from Start to A, which will make you go off course. '''Only bring 0 to 1 DD maximum'''.
*Unfavorable situations WILL HAPPEN.
**If the compass takes you to node J, there are possibilities of being forced to retreat because of one of your ships going into Heavy Damage.
**The enemy Elite Submarines sometimes by rare chance, is able to make one of your ship go into Medium or even Heavy Damage despite being in Echelon or Line Abreast Formation. IT CAN HAPPEN.
*The enemy will attack your support ships, which can damage them bit by bit, even if they are minor damages. However it will build up which will require you to repair the support ships.
*If your Flagship DD or CL somehow goes into Moderate Damage due to getting hit by an enemy in node J or by a Submarine due to some random chance, expect her to have a harder time obtaining MVP due to the lowered damage output.
*'''Do not bring equip any SONAR on CL/CLTs that will reach 100 or higher ASW stats after equipping it'''. This will cause them to be able to attack 3 times via OASW (Opening ASW Strike), stealing MVP from your main DD/CL Flagship. If you are going to bring a CL/CLT who will reach 100 or higher ASW stat, equip them with a Depth Charge instead. 
*Please refrain from bringing Isuzu Kai Ni into this map as a Support Ship due to the reasons stated on the above paragraph. 
==Tips & Recommendations==
*Type 3 Depth Charge and SONAR gives the best output compared to Type 94 Depth Charge and Type 93 SONAR.
*If using BBV, do not equip Zuiun because it will force her to attack submarines instead of the non-submarine enemies.
*If you want faster runs to power level your flagship DD or CL, rotating the support ships with other ships of the same type can make things faster. However beware that repairs may build up in the long run if using too many ships for rotation, which may become a problem for players with only 2 Repair Docks.
*Bringing CLTs as support has potential to minimize the damage done to you in node J.
*Unlike World 3-2A power leveling, this map will require you to either rest your ships every 1 to 2 sorties, or rotate the ships of the same/similar-type. However be warned that rotating too many different ships may cause your repairs to pile up...
*Submarines can minimize the damage done to you by the enemy DD/CLs but is highly risky as Node J contains a Flagship CL equipped with both SONAR and Depth Charge while Submarine Nodes may have 2 CLs in Echelon which can heavily damage your Submarine due to the Formation.

==FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS (FAQ)==
'''1. Why is the BB equipped with a Yellow Gun instead of Two Main Cannons?'''
:It is because if the BB is equipped with two Main Cannons, it has potential to steal MVP away from your Flagship DD/CL when you are facing against the 4 SS + 2 CL or 5 SS + 1 Wa-class Trasnport Ship due to triggering Double Attack. Even by using Cut-in Attack, its damage will be strong but not too big to steal MVP away from the Flagship DD/CL as the BB will most likely only attack once.

'''2. Why can't I use Torpedo Bomber on my CV?'''
:You can but it has high risks of stealing MVP away from your DD/CL because of its potential 1.8x damage multiplier. Dive Bomber only has 1x multiplier, which means moderate damage against the non-Submarine enemies without being huge that could outdamage your DD/CL's ASW damage. If 0.8x multiplier happened from the Torpedo Bomber, you might be safe but if not, then expect MVP getting stolen by your CV. In fact it is worse if you bring a CVL, as it does opening Aerial Bombing + attacks the submarine, which definitely steals MVP majority of the time (Happened to me before in the past). Happened to me before when I tried (Trial and Error!)

'''3. Why are the support CL or CLT equipped with a SONAR? Wouldn't that steal MVP?'''
:If you compare the main flagship DD/CL you are power leveling and the support CL/CLT being equipped with a single ASW equipment, the Flagship DD/CL has more damage output compared to the supporting CL/CLT who only has a single ASW equipment. The reason why the support CL/CLT is equipped with a SONAR is so they can take down even the Elite Submarines with a moderate damage output that's not big as the Flagship DD/CL's ASW damage output. In the past I have brought support CL/CLTs without any ASW equipment on them, but the issue with this was that the Elite (Red) Submarines, especially the Submarine Yo-class Elite, could not be taken down fully, which caused me to obtain only A Rank Victory. However after I added one SONAR to the support CL/CLT, they were able to take down the Elite Submarines without giving much big damage output.

As for stealing MVP, that never really happens unless
*Flagship DD/CL's attack somehow misses (it does happen sometimes...)
*Flagship DD/CL is Moderate/Heavy Damaged.
*CLTs' Pre-emptive Torpedo Strike somehow happens to hit the non-Submarine enemies in the Submarine Nodes (Line Abreast makes rate of Torpedoes hitting the enemy very low)
*Your CL/CLT support has 100+ ASW and has a SONAR equipped. 

'''4. So what is the difference between using a Type 0 Recon Seaplane and using a SONAR on the support CL?'''
:If you want to have the support CL be able to use Double Attack in Node J to increase your survivability there, you could just go with the Type 0 Recon Plane, but if you want more reliability in the support CL taking down the Elite Submarines in the Submarine nodes, then go with SONAR, but expect it will lose its Artillery Spotting Effect as it won't be equipped with a Type 0 Recon Seaplane. [[Ooyodo|Ooyodo Kai]] is exempt from this as she has 4 Equipment Slots which will allow you to equip both Type 0 Recon Seaplane and a SONAR, allowing Double Attack in Node J while supporting your Flagship DD/CL in the Submarine Nodes.
'''5. Can I still use this setup if I don't have a Saiun?'''
:You can, but expect to face some T-Cross Red Disadvantage situations which will most likely make you unable to take down the entire enemy fleet in the Submarine Nodes.
Recommended Recipe for making Saiun is '''20/60/10/111'''.
==Conclusion==
Unlike Power Leveling your BB, CV(L) and CA in World 3-2 Node A, leveling DD/CL is more extensive because of being required to use a bit more resource expensive fleet and having to repair them. You always have World 1-5 to power level your DD/CL, but in the long run it gets very tiring and may take a very long time to level up your ship since the maximum EXP you could get per run is 1620 EXP (node A to C with rank S victory all the time: 540 EXP x3) in contrast to World 4-3's 2376 (2 Submarine Nodes with S Rank Victory: 1188 x2)~2970 (+594 EXP from node J) EXP gain per run.

Also the fact 1-5 is out of the question once you reach Level 80+ HQ unless you are leveling a DD/CL who can reach 100 ASW after equipping 2 SONAR and 1 Depth Charge. 

I use this setup all the time now to power level my DD/CL, and unless some derp situations happen, my DD/CL gets MVP all the time.

